text: Kastor Notter (16 February 1903 - 9 January 1950) was a Swiss racing cyclist. He was the Swiss National Road Race champion in 1924, 1925 and 1927. He finished in fifth place in the 1926 Paris–Roubaix. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1903 births Category:1950 deaths Category:People from Baden District, Aargau Category:Swiss male cyclists
